Gunmen have killed a yet-to-be identified policeman along Eke Oko market in Aguata local government area of Anambra State. Aguata local government area is where Governor Charles Soludo hails from. The incident happened on Sunday around 6.45pm according to sources. According to sources, the policeman was riding his motorcycle along the road when the suspected gunmen shot him. But Anambra Police spokesman Ikenga Tochukwu told The Nation the Command was not aware of any missing policeman.   Presidential primaries (3) Endorsements and conclusion     Muslims who kill Christians in Nigeria over blasphemy…     NFF appoints José Peseiro Super Eagles coach   He said none of the Command’s men had been able to identify the policeman shot dead. However, he said the Command would continue investigation on the killed policeman. An eyewitness who spoke with The Nation in the area, said residents scampered for safety when the gunmen struck. The incident came few days after Soludo visited the leader of Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) Nnamdi Kanu in detention.. Aguata community had been under attack from gunmen for some time.